FBIS4-19064 "drweu071_j_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-071 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Chief Fininvest TV News Editors Resign in Protest Chief Fininvest TV News Editors Resign in Protest LD1304112294 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1030 GMT 13 Apr 94 LD1304112294 Rome RAI Uno Television Network Italian BFN [Text] Mentana, Fede, and Liguori, the chief editors of the news bulletins broadcast on the three Fininvest-controlled television channels [Canale Cinque, Retequattro, and Italia Uno] handed in their resignations a short time ago as a protest against the statements made by Franco Tato, the managing director of the Fininvest group. He told a newspaper that if the Mammi Law [telecommunications law approved last year by parliament] did not exist, he would have cancelled all the news and information programs on the three channels.
